This paper is about creating an empathetic dialog system using a multi-head Transformer architecture. The paper focuses on natural language processing and language generation, which are the main topics of the cs.CL (Computation and Language) sub-category. Additionally, the paper utilizes pre-trained models and machine learning techniques, which are also relevant to the cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) and cs.LG (Machine Learning) sub-categories. The paper also discusses the use of metadata and emotions, which are relevant to the cs.SD (Sound and Music Computing) sub-category. Finally, the paper aims to improve the quality of generated conversations, which is relevant to the cs.HC (Human-Computer Interaction) sub-category.
